headline: IBM Board Refresh And AI Push Highlight Evolving Growth Priorities
summary: IBM (NYSE:IBM) has appointed PepsiCo CEO Ramon L. Laguarta to its board, adding an executive with extensive large scale transformation experience. The company has rolled out new AI focused initiatives, including an agentic AI solution with e& and AI powered fan platforms for the GRAMMYs. These moves highlight IBM's focus on leadership renewal and expansion of its software, AI, and digital consulting activities. headline: PepsiCo Reshapes Global Operations While Shares Trade Below Estimated Value
summary: PepsiCo (NasdaqGS:PEP) plans to cut around 400 jobs in Spain as it shifts to an indirect distribution model. The company has agreed a new biomethane supply deal in the UK with Engie focused on its supply chain operations. PepsiCo recently announced leadership changes in its finance division for India and South Asia. PepsiCo, trading at $153.63, is taking several important steps across key markets at the same time. The company is reshaping parts of its European distribution footprint,...
